Package com.nitrous.gwt.earth.client.api

Interface Summary
BatchFunction Implementations of BatchFunction can be passed to GoogleEarth.executeBatch() to efficiently execute an arbitrary, user-defined function (the batch function), minimizing the amount of overhead incurred during cross-process communication between the web browser and Google Earth Plugin.
GEPluginReadyListener The interface implemented by any object that wishes to be notified of the success or failure of the Google Earth Plugin initialization.
GoogleEarthInitListener The interface that is implemented by any listener that wishes to be notified when the Google Earth plugin initialization is completed.
 

Class Summary
GEAbstractBalloon The base class for the three types of balloon windows that can overlay the 3D window.
GEControl The base class for GETimeControl.
GEEventEmitter Defines when and how an event gets passed in and triggered from the Google Earth Plug-in.
GEFeatureBalloon Base class for GEHtmlStringBalloon and GEHtmlDivBalloon.
GEFeatureContainer A container class that holds one or more features and allows the creation of nested hierarchies.
GEGeometryContainer A container object that contains an array of geometries, typically the children of a multi-geometry.
GEGlobe The GEGlobe class encapsulates the Google Earth globe to determine access and event behavior.
GEHitTestResult This interface contains result information obtained by calling GEView's hitTest method.
GEHtmlBalloon A balloon that contains HTML.
GEHtmlDivBalloon  
GEHtmlStringBalloon The GEHtmlStringBalloon class represents a balloon based on the contentString.
GELinearRingContainer A container object that contains an array of closed line strings, typically the outer boundary of a Polygon.
GENavigationControl Used to manipulate the navigation controls in Google Earth.
GEOptions Used to manipulate the behavior of the Google Earth options such as, navigation, flyToSpeed, scroll wheel speed and so on.
GEPhotoOverlayViewer This interface enables programmatic and user-driven interaction with photo overlays in the Google Earth Plugin.
GEPlugin The GEPlugin is the Google Earth Plugin's main object, and this is the object that is returned to the JavaScript application when you first create a plug-in instance.
GESchemaObject The root class from which all map objects are derived
GESchemaObjectContainer Holds one or more KML objects.
GEStyleSelectorContainer A container that holds a collection of KmlStyle and KmlStyleMap objects.
GESun The GESun class controls the dawn to dusk views.
GETime Controls time in the plugin.
GETimeControl Represents the time slider object.
GETourPlayer This interface enables programmatic and user-driven interaction with KML tours in the Google Earth Plugin.
GETourPlayerControl This interface provides access to the visibility controls of the GE Tour Control.
GEView Controls the behavior of the camera that views the scene in Google Earth.
GEWindow The object corresponding to the retangular region in which Google Earth is displayed.
GoogleEarth An overlay for the google.earth Namespace http://code.google.com/apis/earth/documentation/reference/google_earth_namespace.html
GoogleEarthWidget The widget that allows you to add the Google Earth view to a GWT user interface
KmlAbstractView This is an abstract class and cannot be created directly.
KmlAltitudeGeometry Specifies an AltitudeMode for derived classes.
KmlBalloonOpeningEvent Fired when a description balloon is about to open.
KmlBalloonStyle Specifies how the description balloon for placemarks is drawn.
KmlCamera Defines the camera that views the scene.
KmlColor The KmlColor object values are expressed in hexadecimal notation.
KmlColorStyle The KmlColorStyle object is an abstract object.
KmlContainer An abstract object and cannot be used directly.
KmlCoord A single tuple consisting of floating point values for longitude, latitude, and altitude (in that order).
KmlCoordArray The KmlCoordArray object defines an array of coordinates.
KmlDateTime Represents a specific point in time.
KmlDocument A KmlDocument has containers that holds features and styles.
KmlEvent The event object used with all KMLObjects.
KmlExtrudableGeometry Specifies the behavior of the object's geometry.
KmlFeature The KmlFeature object is an abstract object and is the base for all feature types (for example Placemarks, Overlays, and NetworkLinks).
KmlFolder A Folder is used to arrange other features hierarchically (Folders, Placemarks, NetworkLinks, or Overlays).
KmlGeometry The KmlGeometry object is an abstract object and cannot be used directly.
KmlGroundOverlay Draws an image overlay draped onto the terrain.
KmlIcon Defines an image associated with an Icon style or overlay.
KmlIconStyle Specifies how icons for point placemarks are drawn in Google Earth.
KmlLabelStyle Specifies how the name of a feature is drawn in the 3D viewer.
KmlLatLonAltBox Specifies a bounding box that describes an area of interest defined by geographic coordinates and altitudes.
KmlLatLonBox Specifies the top, bottom, right, and left sides of a bounding box on the Earth's surface.
KmlLayer A layer displayed in Google Earth.
KmlLayerRoot A container for the various layers displayed with the Google Earth Plug-in.
KmlLinearRing Defines a closed line string, typically the outer boundary of a Polygon.
KmlLineString Defines a connected set of line segments.
KmlLineStyle The KmlLineStyle object specifies the drawing style (color, color mode, and line width) for all line geometry.
KmlLink Specifies the location of any KML files fetched by network links, image files used by icons in icon styles, ground overlays, and screen overlays, or model files used in the Model object.
KmlListStyle Specifies how a feature is displayed in the list view.
KmlLocation Specifies the exact coordinates of the Model's origin in latitude, longitude, and altitude.
KmlLod The KmlLod or level of detail, describes the size of the projected region on the screen that is required in order for the region to be considered active.
KmlLookAt Defines a camera that is associated with anything derived from feature.
KmlModel A 3D object described in a referenced COLLADA file.
KmlMouseEvent Represents a mouse input event.
KmlMultiGeometry A container for zero or more geometry primitives associated with the same feature.
KmlNetworkLink References a KML file or KMZ archive on a remote network.
KmlObject The base class for all the other objects in the Google Earth Plug-in.
KmlObjectBase  
KmlObjectList A collection of KmlObjects.
KmlObjectPartial  
KmlOrientation Describes rotation of a 3D model's coordinate system to position the object in Google Earth.
KmlOverlay The KmlOverlay object is an abstract object and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
KmlPhotoOverlay Defines a photo overlay, which is a geographically located photograph of the Earth.
KmlPlacemark The KmlPlacemark is a feature with associated Geometry.
KmlPoint A geographic location defined by longitude, latitude, and (optional) altitude.
KmlPolygon A Polygon is defined by an outer boundary and 0 or more inner boundaries.
KmlPolyStyle Specifies the drawing style for all polygons, including polygon extrusions (which look like the walls of buildings) and line extrusions (which look like solid fences).
KmlRegion The KmlRegion object is used to set region objects and their properties.
KmlScale Scales a model along the x, y, and z axes in the model's coordinate space.
KmlScreenOverlay Draws an image overlay fixed to the screen.
KmlStyle Defines the icon, label, line, list, polygon, and balloon styles.
KmlStyleMap Maps between two different icon styles.
KmlStyleSelector The base class for KmlStyle and KmlStyleMap.
KmlTimePrimitive An abstract object and cannot be used directly in a JavaScript file.
KmlTimeSpan Represents an extent in time bounded by begin and end dateTimes.
KmlTimeStamp Represents a single moment in time.
KmlTour Defines a tour, which is a playlist of scripted camera and update events.
KmlVec2 Defines the x and y coordinates of a 2D vector.
KmlViewerOptions This class controls the display of sunlight, historical imagery, and Street View panoramas in the plugin.
